File: The department says schools are allowed to deviate from this plan for health, safety and social distancing reasons. JOHANNESBURG - The next phase of school reopening will take place next month. Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga says the department will work to ensure everything is ready for pupils who return. On 6 July, most primary and secondary schools will be able to operate. READ: Sadtu wants Eastern Cape schools to shut down Schools for pupils with disabilities will also be reopening next month. The department says schools are allowed to deviate from this plan for health, safety and social distancing reasons. It has promised to continue working with schools to make sure pupils and staff are protected. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.